description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;District Nurse / Community Nursing Sister / Charge Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Registered Nurse seeking an exciting opportunity to work within North East Derbyshire and Chesterfield Community Services?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, this opportunity is for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There has never been a more exciting time to join one of the largest specialist community NHS providers in the country – one that is also among the very best NHS employers, as voted by its own staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Integrated Community Services include experienced Nurses, Community Matrons, Occupational Therapists, Physiotherapists, Clinical Support Workers and Adult Care staff who work collaboratively with GP Practice staff, Acute and Community Hospitals and Derbyshire County Adult Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is to provide nursing care in patients&#39; own homes and residential care home settings, to prevent hospital admissions or facilitate early discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a full time post available across the locality working alongside the Community Nursing Teams but with a special interest in Rapid Response. The role will involve you using your clinical and leadership skills in managing and responding to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Urgent (same day) community nursing referrals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring holistic patient assessment to prevent hospital admissions or facilitate early discharge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-ordinating the nursing response during the shift&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing the caseload and staff as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is based in the community, 7 days per week, covering 08.00–18.30.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gemma Cooke, Integrated Community Manager, 07721 879763&lt;/p&gt;
